VALUES ('81c50125-cbb0-4b61-99c2-1d16f626d2da', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'Drawing on data collected across many years, analysts reported a result that complicates the tidy account found in older textbooks. Several nocturnal desert mammals have evolved striking physiological strategies for conserving scarce water through the hottest months. ______ the kangaroo rat extracts nearly all the moisture it needs from dry seeds, rarely drinking free water at all.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"Qualifying the sweeping claim made in the prior sentence with added nuance,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Synonym Trap] Qualifying the sweeping claim made in the prior sentence with added nuance, This phrase suggests a different rhetorical relationship than the one required between the two clauses."},{"id":"B","text":"Building directly on the mechanism described above in the preceding analysis,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Category Shift] Building directly on the mechanism described above in the preceding analysis, This phrase suggests a different rhetorical relationship than the one required between the two clauses."},{"id":"C","text":"Adding a parallel example that deepens the same point about methodological limits,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Register Clash] Adding a parallel example that deepens the same point about methodological limits, This phrase suggests a different rhetorical relationship than the one required between the two clauses."},{"id":"D","text":"Grounding the general statement in a specific instance the researchers documented,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (D). Grounding the general statement in a specific instance the researchers documented, This participial phrase signals example while preserving sentence grammar, matching Digital SAT hard transition expectations."}]'::jsonb, 'D', 'Step 1 — Identify the relationship
Focus on {{yellow:Several}} in the passage. The transition item asks you to identify the relationship before comparing choices.

Step 2 — Test transition logic
Compare each option against explicit textual evidence. On hard items, correct answers usually restate the passage faithfully without absolute words the text does not support.

Step 3 — Complete the sentence
Choice D is correct: Grounding the general statement in a specific instance the researchers documented,.

Distractor analysis:
- A: [Synonym Trap] Qualifying the sweeping claim made in the prior sentence with added nuance, This phrase suggests a different rhetorical relationship than the one required between the two clauses.
- B: [Category Shift] Building directly on the mechanism described above in the preceding analysis, This phrase suggests a different rhetorical relationship than the one required between the two clauses.
- C: [Register Clash] Adding a parallel example that deepens the same point about methodological limits, This phrase suggests a different rhetorical relationship than the one required between the two clauses.', NULL, 'Expression of Ideas', 'Transitions', 'reading_writing', 'expression', 'TRA', NULL, 'hard', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"rw_subtype":"transition","dsat_blueprint_v1":true,"rw_format":"transition_blank","explanation_v2":true,"generator":"regenerate-english-fresh.mjs","regen_phase2":true,"regen_agent":9,"regen_seed_offset":100000}'::jsonb, now(), now());
