VALUES ('29013152-1938-47d5-bc88-11982c08acc4', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'A study published this year set out to test an assumption that practitioners had accepted with little scrutiny for years. Prolonged drought sharply reduced the flowering plants that the region''s native bees depend on for nectar each spring. ______ local pollinator numbers declined steeply, and nearby orchards reported their thinnest fruit set in more than a decade.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"Qualifying the sweeping claim made in the prior sentence with added nuance,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Synonym Trap] Qualifying the sweeping claim made in the prior sentence with added nuance, This phrase suggests a different rhetorical relationship than the one required between the two clauses."},{"id":"B","text":"Extending the causal chain the author has begun to trace across the study,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (B). Extending the causal chain the author has begun to trace across the study, This participial phrase signals cause while preserving sentence grammar, matching Digital SAT hard transition expectations."},{"id":"C","text":"Adding a parallel example that deepens the same point about methodological limits,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Category Shift] Adding a parallel example that deepens the same point about methodological limits, This phrase suggests a different rhetorical relationship than the one required between the two clauses."},{"id":"D","text":"Blurring the sharp contrast the passage has drawn between the two claims,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Register Clash] Blurring the sharp contrast the passage has drawn between the two claims, This phrase suggests a different rhetorical relationship than the one required between the two clauses."}]'::jsonb, 'B', 'Step 1 — Identify the relationship
Focus on {{yellow:drought}} in the passage. The transition item asks you to identify the relationship before comparing choices.

Step 2 — Test transition logic
Compare each option against explicit textual evidence. On hard items, correct answers usually restate the passage faithfully without absolute words the text does not support.

Step 3 — Complete the sentence
Choice B is correct: Extending the causal chain the author has begun to trace across the study,.

Distractor analysis:
- A: [Synonym Trap] Qualifying the sweeping claim made in the prior sentence with added nuance, This phrase suggests a different rhetorical relationship than the one required between the two clauses.
- C: [Category Shift] Adding a parallel example that deepens the same point about methodological limits, This phrase suggests a different rhetorical relationship than the one required between the two clauses.
- D: [Register Clash] Blurring the sharp contrast the passage has drawn between the two claims, This phrase suggests a different rhetorical relationship than the one required between the two clauses.', NULL, 'Expression of Ideas', 'Transitions', 'reading_writing', 'expression', 'TRA', NULL, 'hard', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"rw_subtype":"transition","dsat_blueprint_v1":true,"rw_format":"transition_blank","explanation_v2":true,"generator":"regenerate-english-fresh.mjs","regen_phase2":true,"regen_agent":9,"regen_seed_offset":100000}'::jsonb, now(), now());
